verses.text_plain: Praise ye the Lord. Praise the Lord, O my soul.
verses.verse_html:
1Praise ye the Lord. Praise the Lord, O my soul. ▼
▼ Praise ye…: Heb. Hallelujah

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Praise ye…: Heb. Hallelujah

verses.text_plain: While I live will I praise the Lord: I will sing praises unto my God while I have any being.
verses.verse_html: 2While I live will I praise the Lord: I will sing praises unto my God while I have any being.

verses.text_plain: Put not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom there is no help.
verses.verse_html:
3Put not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom there is no help. ▼
▼ help: or, salvation

verses.text_plain: His breath goeth forth, he returneth to his earth; in that very day his thoughts perish.
verses.verse_html: 4His breath goeth forth, he returneth to his earth; in that very day his thoughts perish.

verses.text_plain: Happy is he that hath the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope is in the Lord his God:
verses.verse_html: 5Happy is he that hath the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope is in the Lord his God:

verses.text_plain: Which made heaven, and earth, the sea, and all that therein is: which keepeth truth for ever:
verses.verse_html: 6Which made heaven, and earth, the sea, and all that therein is: which keepeth truth for ever:

verses.text_plain: Which executeth judgment for the oppressed: which giveth food to the hungry. The Lord looseth the prisoners:
verses.verse_html: 7Which executeth judgment for the oppressed: which giveth food to the hungry. The Lord looseth the prisoners:

verses.text_plain: The Lord openeth the eyes of the blind: the Lord raiseth them that are bowed down: the Lord loveth the righteous:
verses.verse_html: 8The Lord openeth the eyes of the blind: the Lord raiseth them that are bowed down: the Lord loveth the righteous:

verses.text_plain: The Lord preserveth the strangers; he relieveth the fatherless and widow: but the way of the wicked he turneth upside down.
verses.verse_html: 9The Lord preserveth the strangers; he relieveth the fatherless and widow: but the way of the wicked he turneth upside down.

verses.text_plain: The Lord shall reign for ever, even thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 10The Lord shall reign for ever, even thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise ye the Lord.
